Welcome!
This is Katherine’s appendix area for additional visualizations and non-visualization code. The research here may prove useful for audiences, but it is complementary to the main findings located in the main index.
Non-Graph: Which states lead for lowest, moderate, and highest AI adoption rates?

Code# Which states have the LOWEST AI adoption rates? Non-Graph. 
k_tech_2018_clean |&gt; 
    # Grouping for total amounts. 
  group_by(state) |&gt;
  mutate(overall_state_total = sum(n_firms, na.rm = TRUE)) |&gt;
  ungroup() |&gt;
  group_by(state, naics_sector) |&gt;
  mutate(
    state_industry_total = sum(n_firms, na.rm = TRUE),
    pct_of_industry = (n_firms / state_industry_total) * 100) |&gt;
  ungroup() |&gt; 
    # data cleaning 
  filter(tech_type == "artificial intelligence") |&gt; 
  filter(naics_sector != "Total") |&gt; 
  filter(naics_sector != "Other") |&gt; 
  filter(!is.na(use_level)) |&gt; 
  filter(!is.na(n_firms)) |&gt; 
  filter(use_level == "Did not use") |&gt; 
    # creating groups for summaries 
  group_by(state_label) |&gt; 
  summarize(
    state_non_users = sum(n_firms, na.rm = TRUE),
    state_total_all_firms = first(overall_state_total),
    nonusers_to_allfirms = (state_non_users / state_total_all_firms)) |&gt;
  arrange(desc(nonusers_to_allfirms)) |&gt; 
  head(3)

# A tibble: 3 × 4
  state_label state_non_users state_total_all_firms nonusers_to_allfirms
  &lt;chr&gt;                 &lt;dbl&gt;                 &lt;dbl&gt;                &lt;dbl&gt;
1 Wyoming               11474                 11681                0.982
2 Alaska                11127                 11402                0.976
3 Montana               23784                 24489                0.971

